        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Codex archived usage undercount",
        "body": "Fixes #1767\n\n## Summary\n\n- Keep Codex cache-read tokens as separately priced billable input instead of clamping them to non-cached input.\n- De-duplicate active and archived session files at row identity granularity, preserving legitimate same-turn equal deltas while removing replayed rows.\n- Scope files without session metadata by file identity so unrelated logs cannot suppress each other.\n- Preserve cached days outside narrow scan windows and rescan cached sessions that contain usage but lack stable row identity.\n- Force a safe rescan when fork metadata or archive overlap makes an incremental append ambiguous.\n- Regenerate the parser fingerprint after integrating current `main`, including the Sakana provider changes.\n\n## Validation\n\n- All 48 `CostUsageScannerBreakdownTests`\n- `make check`\n- Live local-data proof on the repaired scanner: a forced 30-day scan and immediate warm-cache scan produced identical normalized totals and daily buckets, with cache-read tokens represented. Raw private usage and cost values were intentionally not posted.\n- Exact-head automated review requested after integrating current `main`.\n",
